---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import ProjectHero from '../../../../components/ProjectHero.astro';
import SubGrid from '../../../../components/SubGrid.astro';
import type { SubCard } from '../../../../components/SubGrid.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const IMG = (p: string) => `/japoneson/images/wp/${p}`;

const subCards: SubCard[] = [
  {
    title: 'FLUTE',
    image: IMG('2024/02/03-e1707925750233.jpg'),
    imageAlt: 'Flute',
    description:
      '"Just you go play the flute, I\'ll sell some smack and buy you a good flute with the money." — Almost Transparent Blue (1976)',
    href: '/en/murakami/tosco/flute/',
  },
  {
    title: '"The Man" who called "TOSCO"',
    subtitle: 'José Luis Cortés (1994)',
    image: IMG('2024/01/1994-jose-luis_500.jpg'),
    imageAlt: 'José Luis Cortés Tosco',
    description:
      'The flutist, bandleader, composer — the "New World Beat" that exists nowhere else but inside this one man.',
    href: '/en/murakami/music/the-man-who-called-tosco/',
  },
  {
    title: 'TOSCO ⊂ MURAKAMI = "KYOKO"',
    image: IMG('2026/05/kyoko05-1024x697.jpg'),
    imageAlt: 'KYOKO film scene with Tosco',
    description:
      'Tosco, KYOKO, and Ryu Murakami — stories all connected. Tosco lives inside Murakami; Murakami lives inside Tosco\'s music.',
    href: '/en/murakami/tosco/kyoko-02/',
  },
];

const trail = [
  { slug: 'murakami', title: 'MURAKAMI MAMBO !!', path: `${base}en/murakami/` },
  { slug: 'tosco', title: 'Tosco & Murakami', path: `${base}en/murakami/tosco/` },
];
---

<Layout title='Tosco &amp; Murakami — Japonéson' lang="en">
  <Header lang="en" />
  <main>
    <ProjectHero
      kicker="EARLY 1990S · THE SPECIAL PERIOD"
      title="Tosco y Murakami"
      subtitle="A bond born in the Special Period — Ryu Murakami and José Luis Cortés."
      image={`${base}images/murakami/hero_tosco.jpg`}
      align="center"
      height={850}
    />

    <div class="container breadcrumb-wrap">
      <Breadcrumb trail={trail} lang="en" />
    </div>

    <section class="intro">
      <div class="intro-inner">
        <p class="opener">
          It began with a single line I found online, in an article published four
          years before José Luis Cortés (TOSCO) passed away
          (<a class="src-link" href="https://oncubanews.com/cultura/musica/tosco-y-cortes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tosco y Cortés | OnCuba News</a>).
        </p>
        <blockquote class="opener-quote">
          "He has thirteen flutes, but during a tour he lost his favorite one.
          'Murakami told me I had to have the best flute in the world, and he bought
          me one made entirely of silver.'"
        </blockquote>
        <p class="opener-close">I wanted to know more about the two of them.</p>
        <p>
          Early 1990s. It was the "Special Period" in Cuba — a time of great hardship
          following the collapse of the Soviet Union. In the midst of this era, two
          men met: <strong>Ryu Murakami</strong> and <strong>José Luis Cortés "Tosco."</strong>
          Together, they created countless recordings and unforgettable concerts.
        </p>
        <p>
          I feel their meeting was destiny, like two souls pulling together exactly
          what they needed. Their bond was incredibly strong. Interestingly, a scene
          from Ryu Murakami's debut novel, <em>Almost Transparent Blue</em>, feels
          like a "foreshadowing" of their meeting — as if their friendship was
          written in the stars long before it happened.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe the friendship and collaboration between these two became a
          vital piece of Cuban music history in the 1990s. I hope you can feel the
          deep bond that existed between them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <SubGrid cards={subCards} columns={3} />

    <section class="excerpt">
      <div class="excerpt-inner">
        <h2>The New World Beat: A Guide to Pleasurable Cuban Music</h2>
        <p class="excerpt-meta"><em>Excerpt from Ryu Murakami's 1993 essay.</em></p>

        <blockquote>
          <p>
            "He is my dear friend; the two of us call each other brothers. José Luis
            is a bandleader, songwriter, composer, arranger, and flutist (as well
            as a singer, dancer, and baritone saxophonist). He is world-class in
            every one of these roles, but as a flutist he is, without question,
            a genius — the best in the world, beyond anyone's reach.
          </p>
          <p>
            Countless times, while spending time with him, I've thought, 'So this is
            what true talent looks like.' Because he pays no mind at all to pleasing
            others, in Cuba he is misunderstood as a cocky upstart — but at his core
            he is incredibly kind.
          </p>
          <p>
            When the album <em>You Don't Know What Love Is</em> was recorded in
            Havana with the voice of Xiomara Laugart, he served as music director
            and did perfect work. I mean 'perfect' in the truest sense of the word.
            Drilled in the classics, he tosses off jazz as if it were nothing —
            almost as though sneering at jazz itself — a true child of music.
          </p>
          <p>
            Today, the fusion of the African and the European — that is, the
            'New World Beat,' the new music that will come after the classical —
            exists nowhere but inside José Luis Cortés. Whenever I tell him this,
            he always laughs, embarrassed, but he clearly carries a certain pride
            within him.
          </p>
          <p>
            I love his favorite saying:
            <strong>'Don't mess with me — I'm amazing.'</strong>
          </p>
          <footer>— Ryu Murakami, 1993</footer>
        </blockquote>

        <h2>About Tosco</h2>
        <p>
          Born on October 5, 1951, in Santa Clara, Cuba, and passed away on April 18,
          2022, at the age of 70. He was affectionately known as <strong>"Tosco."</strong>
          His nickname, which means "rough" or "gruff," reflected his blunt and
          straightforward personality. As the leader of <strong>NG La Banda</strong>,
          he perfected the musical style known as <strong>"Timba."</strong>
          Today, José Luis Cortés is revered by the Cuban people as a legendary musician.
        </p>
        <p>
          Two of NG La Banda's masterpieces — <em>Cabaret Panorámico | Échale Limón</em>
          (1993) and <em>La Bruja</em> — were produced by Ryu Murakami. The track
          "Murakami Mambo" is featured on the <em>Cabaret Panorámico</em> album.
        </p>

        <figure class="photo">
          <img
            src="/japoneson/images/wp/2024/02/IMG_4314-1-scaled-e1707925954739.jpg"
            alt="TOSCO & Seina, 2014"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>TOSCO &amp; Seina (2014)</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang="en" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .breadcrumb-wrap { padding-top: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0; }

  .intro {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 1rem;
  }
  .intro-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .opener {
    font-family: var(--font-display-cinzel);
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .opener .src-link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }
  .opener .src-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }
  .opener-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-italic-quote);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 28px;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.55;
    border: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    margin: 2.5rem auto;
    max-width: 720px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .opener-quote::before,
  .opener-quote::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    width: 80px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .opener-quote::before { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .opener-quote::after { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .intro-inner p.opener-close {
    font-family: var(--font-italic-quote);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 2rem 0 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .opener-quote { font-size: 21px; padding: 1rem 0.5rem; }
  }
  .intro-inner p {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }

  .excerpt {
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }
  .excerpt-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .excerpt-inner h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display-cinzel);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .excerpt-meta {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .excerpt-inner p {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }
  blockquote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-italic-quote);
    font-style: italic;
    color: #444;
  }
  blockquote p {
    font-family: var(--font-italic-quote) !important;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 19px !important;
    line-height: 1.75 !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem !important;
  }
  blockquote footer {
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }
  .photo {
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .photo img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .photo figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-display-cinzel);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .opener { font-size: 16px; }
    .opener-quote { font-size: 17px; }
    .excerpt-inner h2 { font-size: 22px; }
  }
</style>
